

********* API ***************

An application programming interface (API) is a particular set of rules ('code') and specifications that software programs can follow to communicate with each other. It  

serves as an interface between different software programs and facilitates their interaction, similar to the way the user interface facilitates interaction between humans 

and computers.

It is just a way to communicate between two software components .

It can be of any form ex: CLI


